==English==

===Etymology=== 
From the Latin ''[[exstirpare]]'' "uproot"; ''[[ex-]]'' "out of" + ''[[stirp-]]'' "roots"

===Verb===
{{en-verb|extirpat|ing}}
# to pull up by the roots; [[uproot]]
# to [[destroy]] completely; to [[annihilate]]
# to [[surgically]] remove

====Synonyms====
*[[extricate]] (1)
*[[destroy]] (2)
*[[excise]] (3)

===Derived terms===
*[[extirpation]] (n)
*[[extirpator]] (n)
*[[extirpative]] (adj)

